		<a href="MB_editmsg.asp?FID=69&FN=Rogue&SID=7&SN=EverQuest&TID=1246009&TN=Hide%2FSneak+question&CAT=Classes&SURL=http%3A%2F%2Fwww%2Eeverlore%2Ecom&MSID=2041845&PL=4">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/edit.gif" border="0" alt="Edit/Delete Message" width="18" height="13"></a>
		
		</font>
		<hr size="1">Sneak and then Hide. This will make you invis to most mobs except many found in PoP (ALWAYS con mobs before approaching to be safe). Shroud of Stealth helps tackle the remaining mobs that sneak/hide wont help with...but you can still be seen by many mobs in PoP even with SoS (Tier 3 and up PoP zones).</P><P>I have made it a habit to leave sneak on most of the time (when in groups). Ive found this reduces the chances of being picked on by wandering mobs or other adds.</P><P>Sneaking makes you "invis" to mobs that do not have you directly in their line-of-sight but walking in front of them without having hidin as well, will draw aggro.</P><P>The line-of-sight issue while sneaking is how a Rogue can single pull mobs. Often called "sneak pulling". Though sneak pulling can be tricky in some dungeons ive found that it works rather well. Just dont tell anyone...we want to keep the other classes pulling for us <img src='http://www.everlore.com/gimages/wink.gif' width=15 height=15 align=middle></P><P>That pretty much beats the subject of sneak/hide to death. Hope this helps.<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
